body:
it's worth noting that a somewhat stable "workaround" for this, that shouldn't break when this gets fixed would be to give the field you're selecting an alias, and returning it like so:

```php
$query = $em->createQuery('SELECT COUNT(u.id) AS count, u.age AS HIDDEN userAge FROM MyProject\Model\User u HAVING userAge > 20');

$singleScalarResult = $query->getResult()[0]['count'];
```
